{
  "texts": [
    "AE detection is considered as a more difficult task for LLMs compared with other entities used in this study (as drug, dose, or indication) [32].",
    "For complex NER tasks, the significant performance increase would likely justify the higher GPT 4 costs and longer execution time per request compared with GPT 3.5.",
    "For AE detection, zero-shot Zephyr demonstrates better performance than GPT 3.5 and could alternatively be used.",
    "With the given prompt, we observed similar F1 performances of zero-shot GPT 4 and fine-tuned T5 for nonproduct combination entities, while the product combination scores of T5 are significantly higher compared with all other models.",
    "The results imply that compared with a small T5-Base with complete weight fine-tuning performance, QLoRA fine-tuned models could not achieve comparable performance especially with regard to production combination entities."
  ]
}